1
00:00:01,166 --> 00:00:03,875
Of course, they didn’t bring me through
this door, they brought me through that one

2
00:00:04,791 --> 00:00:07,875
They brought me in from here, I wasn’t blindfolded yet

3
00:00:09,208 --> 00:00:14,375
They stopped me right here and blindfolded me before taking me
through the main door leading to the solitary cells and the rest

4
00:00:15,958 --> 00:00:20,666
They stopped me right here, exactly here, and blindfolded me

5
00:00:21,916 --> 00:00:27,833
They blindfolded me and took me
inside, and after they’d taken me inside

6
00:00:28,958 --> 00:00:35,833
They took me into the interrogation room while I was still
blindfolded, a room that had a <i>majlis</i> [furniture set]

7
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:45,375
Here, the first thing I saw was this door,
that’s how I knew I had entered from here

8
00:00:45,416 --> 00:00:49,666
But inside, I didn’t know what was there, I just walked
straight ahead, they didn’t take me right or left

9
00:00:53,916 --> 00:00:57,208
We came out from here, straight
ahead like this, then I walked to the right

10
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:02,000
Exactly from this spot, we entered through that door

11
00:01:06,625 --> 00:01:09,916
We arrived here, of course I couldn’t hear any sounds, nothing at all

12
00:01:09,958 --> 00:01:14,541
Only their voices beside me, they took me into this room

13
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,291
This is the room on the right, we entered through the door

14
00:01:28,541 --> 00:01:32,583
The door was in this spot, I think, around here

15
00:01:38,791 --> 00:01:45,416
They brought me in and made me sit here, then
they left, after about two or three minutes

16
00:01:46,125 --> 00:01:53,000
Here I slightly lifted the blindfold and looked around,
I saw a <i>majlis</i> [furniture set], the room was tidy

17
00:01:54,291 --> 00:01:57,416
I heard their voices coming, around eight of them approached me

18
00:01:58,791 --> 00:02:02,666
They sat beside me while I was blindfolded
and started asking me several questions

19
00:02:03,166 --> 00:02:07,750
Like, what’s your name? Are you
married or not? And questions like that

20
00:02:07,791 --> 00:02:14,958
Then they started asking questions like, Do you have relatives in the Free
Syrian Army? Do you have relatives in regime areas? Questions like these

21
00:02:16,708 --> 00:02:19,333
Interviewer: How many people were here?

22
00:02:19,458 --> 00:02:20,958
Witness: You mean in the room I was in?

23
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,916
Interviewer: Where were these people from?
Witness: Yes, in this room

24
00:02:25,041 --> 00:02:32,500
In this room, it was me and eight of them, because
each one asked me a question, so I knew they were eight

25
00:02:33,625 --> 00:02:39,958
A little while later, after they’d finished interrogating
me, one of them left and said, Bring him some tea

26
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:46,416
One or two of them went, I don’t know
exactly how many, I don’t remember

27
00:02:47,875 --> 00:02:51,208
They removed my blindfold and brought me a cup of tea

28
00:02:52,208 --> 00:02:54,750
He told me, Drink the tea. I drank,
and he started asking me questions

29
00:02:54,791 --> 00:02:58,250
Like, Didn’t you go to the Free Syrian Army? Are
your relatives in the Free Syrian Army? And so on

30
00:02:59,666 --> 00:03:02,416
Two of them, I think, knew me, of course they were all masked

31
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:07,541
After they’d finished asking questions,
they took me back to the solitary cell

32
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:10,416
Interviewer: Was there an audio or video recording, for example?

33
00:03:10,458 --> 00:03:16,541
There was no video, no, audio recording I’m not sure, but
there was no video, no cameras, and they didn’t film me
